			<p>I would like to thank Dr. Fitzsimmons for his detailed response to my earlier query. I would like to comment on his response and would invite Dr. Fitzsommons to comment further if he wishes.</p>
<p>It is apparent to me that dispite the exhaustive process that each appliction to Harvard receives, and as described by Dr. Fitzsimmons,, the criteria used in the evaluation the process, and the specific criteria used in each case to decide on whether or not to admit a student, remain hidden from us and the applicant. Thus most students have no rational way of evaluating their individual chances of being admitted.</p>
